        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I don't know about the other guys, but my story goes like this. You see, I was born the son of a sharecropper. Things never came easy for my family, but while my brothers were out working in the fields growing mashed potatoes and pizza, my brother Bruti and I were doing our own thing... we didn't like the life of a farmer.</P><P>I was what you would call a pyromaniac. I used to light dragon ants and muck worms on fire while Bruti would spend all day fiddling with his staff and reading the bible. He eventually left home and joined the Defenders of Albion. I didn't see him for a long time after that.</P><P>After I "accidentally" burned down my dad's crop of wild sows, he kicked me off the farm. I was forced to do odd jobs to pay my rent: washing horses, polishing swords, even whoring. But no matter what I did, I wasn't happy unless I was setting something on fire. </P><P>That's when I learned about the Academy. I joined up and was trained to put my fire-starting skills to a good use. While the pay wasn't great, the job was something I loved. With this new, steady job, I began spending money like nobody's business... new staves, cloaks, lots of food, you name it! I again found myself strapped for cash.</P><P>I ran into this out-of-work, down-on-his-luck circus geek one day and we started talking. He said his name was Stenchy and that he was looking for perfomers to join his new traveling circus. He said the pay was lousey but the room and board would be free. Well, one thing led to another and whaddaya know, he hired me to shoot apples of someone's head with my fireballs. And who do you think that somebody was... my long, lost brother Bruti. Somehow his path led to Stenchy as well, but that's a story for another day.</P><P><img src="http://www.allizdog.com/daoc/waplespunk/images/Waplespunk_Logo.jpg"><BR>Waplespunk the Yellow - Grillmaster of Stenchy's Traveling Circus<BR>Bruti - Stirfriar in Stenchy's Traveling Circus<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
